title: 2020–21 Pro50 Championship
text:
The 2020–21 Pro50 Championship was the nineteenth edition of the <a href="Pro50%20Championship">Pro50 Championship</a>, a <a href="List%20A%20cricket">List A</a> cricket tournament that was played in <a href="Zimbabwe">Zimbabwe</a>. It started on 18 April 2021, with five teams taking part, and was the final domestic tournament in Zimbabwe's cricket calendar for the 2020–21 season. There was no defending champion, as the <a href="2019%E2%80%9320%20Pro50%20Championship">previous tournament</a> was voided due to the <a href="COVID-19%20pandemic">COVID-19 pandemic</a>.
Following the conclusion of the group stage, <a href="Matabeleland%20Tuskers">Tuskers</a> and <a href="Mashonaland%20Eagles">Eagles</a> advanced to the third-place play-off, and <a href="Southern%20Rocks">Rocks</a> and <a href="Mid%20West%20Rhinos">Rhinos</a> qualified for the final of the tournament. Rhinos won the tournament, beating Rocks by 47 runs in the final.
